ist of numerical data organised in columns with a name plus number next to them like this kaggle example [https://www.kaggle.com/c/digit-recognizer/data](https://www.kaggle.com/c/digit-recognizer/data) the yaml file needs thousands of lines to include all the variables.In the example provided every pixel has its own column so you have column names such as pixel455 etc.While it is easy to make a python script to automatically create the required yaml file it would be far easier for a native way to handle this.There is a huge variety of datasets with the same naming convection for their columns.\r\n\r\nMy idea is to give the user the ability to set a range for similarly named columns  using only one entry on the yaml configuration.Something like this \r\n`name:  pixel`\r\n`range: [0:1000]`\r\n`category:  numerical`\r\n\r\nThis will include column names pixel0,pixel1,pixel2 etc.\r\nWhile I would love to help in the development of such a feature I lack the required knowledge.\r\n","closed_by":{"login":"Denniso2","id":42325785,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQyMzI1Nzg1","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/42325785?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Denniso2","html_url":"https://github.com/Denniso2","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Denniso2/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Denniso2/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Denniso2/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Denniso2/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Denniso2/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Denniso2/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Denniso2/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Denniso2/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Denniso2/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ludwig-ai/ludwig/issues/197/reactions",